## Required Output Format

Output ONLY the following XML block. Do NOT include preamble, commentary, or markdown code fences.

```xml
<fitness_evaluation>
  <score>3</score>
  <rationale>The narrative covers the main agreement areas well but drops several synthesis claims entirely. Claims C7, C11, and C14 from the synthesis have no corresponding content in the narrative. The uncertainties section from the synthesis is compressed into a single sentence, losing important nuance about methodological limitations.</rationale>
  <suggestions>
    <suggestion>Claims C7, C11, and C14 are absent from the narrative; incorporate their content in the relevant sections</suggestion>
    <suggestion>Expand the uncertainties discussion — the synthesis flags three distinct types of uncertainty that are collapsed into one sentence</suggestion>
  </suggestions>
</fitness_evaluation>
```

### ⚠️ CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS

- **Output ONLY the `<fitness_evaluation>` XML block.** No preamble, no markdown fences, no commentary.
- **`<score>` must be an integer from 1-5** (use the Score Conversion table in the rubric above).
- **`<rationale>` must reference claim IDs** when identifying issues.
- **Each `<suggestion>` must be actionable** — cite the specific claim IDs and what to change.

